 [_disableInitializers](https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/5.x/api/proxy#Initializable-_disableInitializers--) for more info
 @custom:oz-upgrades-unsafe-allow constructor

@custom:function-name initialize
@param initialAdmin the admin account | Recommended to be a Multi-Sig Wallet
@param _feeReceiver the fee receiver
@param initialBot the bot that will interact with the controller
@dev this is used in palce of a constructor to initialize a proxy's state using this implemetation's logic

@custom:function-name _authorizeUpgrade
@param newImplementation implementation address
@dev this is a function required by solidity and the openzeppelin UUPS contract
this is used to prevent unauthorized account to upgrade the contract

@custom:function-name changeControllerOwner
@param newOwner new controller owner
@dev this function is used to tranfer ownership and all roles from one account to another while also
removing all permissions on the previous account

@custom:function-name setMulticallAddress
@param newMulticallContract the new multicall contract address
@dev this function is used to change the multicall contract address used by the contract

@custom:function-name setFeeReceiver
@param newFeeReceiver the new fee receiver address
@dev this function is used to change the fee receiver address

@custom:function-name addControllerRole
@param role 0 - BOT | 1 - Caller | 2 - ERC
@param account account to give role to
@dev this function is used to add controller roles with ease in place of grantRole

@custom:function-name removeControllerRole
@param role 0 - BOT | 1 - Caller | 2 - ERC
@param account account to remove role for
@dev this function is used to remove controller roles with ease in place of revokeRole

@custom:function-name multicallAddress
@return multicall the multicall address the controller is using
@dev this function is used to check which multicall contract the controller is using

@custom:function-name removeControllerRole
@param role 0 - BOT | 1 - Caller | 2 - ERC
@param account account to check role against
@return hasControllerRole the bool result if the controller has the role
@dev this function is used to check if an account has a specific controller role

@custom:function-name owner
@return owner address of the current owner/admin of the contract
@dev this function shows the current owner/admin of the contract

@custom:function-name feeReceiver
@return reeReceiver the fee receiver used as reference for fee receivers on factory
generated contracts that's called by the controller contract
@dev this function is used to get the current fee receiver set on the controller contract

@custom:function-name call
@param targetContract the target contract being called by the controller
@param callData the call data
@return data the return data from the call
@dev this function is used to call other contracts from the controller contract

@custom:function-name callBatch
@param calls an array of multicall3 call parameters
@custom:sub-param `target` - the target contract
@custom:sub-param `allowFailure` - whether to allow failure or not
@custom:sub-param `callData` - the call data to pass on the call
@return multicall3ReturnData the multicall3 return data
@dev this function is used to batch call other contracts using multicall3

@custom:function-name callBatch
@param calls an array of multicall3 call with value parameters
@custom:sub-param `target` - the target contract
@custom:sub-param `allowFailure` - whether to allow failure or not
@custom:sub-param `value` - the msg.value or the ETH amount to send
@custom:sub-param `callData` - the call data to pass on the call
@return multicall3ReturnData the multicall3 return data
@dev this function is used to batch call other contracts using multicall3 with value

@custom:function-name transferERC20Token
@param tokenAddress the ERC20 token address
@param receiver the receiver of the token
@param amount the amount of tokens to send
@dev this function is used to transfer ERC20 tokens owned by the controller contract to another address

@custom:function-name vaultReward
@param targetVault the target vault contract
@param to the reward's receiver
@param amount the amount of reward to send
@dev this function is used to interact with a target vault's single target reward function

@custom:function-name vaultRewardBatch
@param targetVault the target vault contract
@param receivers the reward receiver's info
@custom:sub-param `receiver` - receiver's address
@custom:sub-param `amount` - amount of reward
@dev this function is used to interact with a target vault's batch target reward function

@custom:function-name createVault
@param targetVaultFactory the address of the vault factory used to create the vault
@param projectOwner the owner the the vault
@param rewardToken the erc20 token address to reward users with
@param projectName the project name of the vault
@return vault the address of the created vault
@dev this function is used by the controller to create vaults on behalf of the users

